{\*\ftnsep\chftnsep}\pgndec\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
009_Creep and Burrow}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video I present the changes to Creep and Burrow.\line The creep generation of Overlords and Burrow is hardly ever used. What you frequently see is the spread of creep with tumors, because all Zerg ground units move faster on it. But apart from that, not many interesting strategies emerge. In addition, an increased movement speed mainly benefits melee units, which for Zerg are Zerglings, Banelings, Broodlings, Locusts and Ultralisks. In addition, good creep spread ensures that the Zerg army can quickly move from one base to another, which would also be possible through Nydus Worms and Nydus Canals, but due to the long load and unload time, it sometimes even takes longer than moving the army across creep.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Because all of this provided too few advantages and allowed too few playstyles, creep was changed so that Zerg ground units regenerate health faster on creep instead of moving faster. This improves hit-and-run strategies and also increases the usefulness of the Overlord\u8217\'92s Generate Creep ability, whether in the opponent\u8217\'92s base to keep Zerg units alive longer, or outside of combat to help them regenerate more quickly. Another advantage is that not only melee units benefit strongly from creep, but all Zerg ground units, and not only during a fight, but also afterwards.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To make Burrow more interesting, the damage dealt to all burrowed units, including the Widow Mine, is reduced by 50%. In addition, all Zerg ground units receive a speed bonus for a few seconds after unburrowing, allowing them to either launch a quick attack or retreat swiftly. However, this boost is only granted if the Zerg unit has been burrowed for a short time beforehand. As a result, it becomes worthwhile to burrow Zerg units when they are standing idle, so that in case of an attack they can either escape more quickly or get into attack range faster. This gives Burrow a purpose even if the burrowed Zerg units are revealed.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
These changes ensure that Overlord creep spread and Burrow have greater usefulness and also enhance immersion, since hiding underground and spreading creep, especially into enemy bases, are key characteristics of the Zerg. Now, you will see them more frequently in the game because they bring a greater advantage when used.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
010+020_Spine Crawler and Spore Crawler}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\loch

\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In today\u8217\'92s video, I present the changes to the Spine and Spore Crawler.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
\line The Spine Crawler has been made larger so that it can block units in the mineral line more effectively and also appear more threatening. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The Spore Crawler has received more health so that it performs better against air units and makes players less reliant on Queens and their Transfuse ability. To prevent it from being mass-produced too easily, however, its cost has been increased. In my opinion, it was previously too easy to build large numbers of Spore Crawlers, and even though the Zerg are known for strength in numbers rather than quality, the Spore Crawler, with its mobility and detection ability, was simply too cheap. Building static defenses should be a real commitment, and until now that was too minor in the case of the Spore Crawler. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
030_Overlord}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In today\u8217\'92s video, I present the changes to the Overlord.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Up until now, the Overlord could be used very effectively as an early scouting unit without requiring much attention. In addition, the Creep Generation ability was rarely used, as the speed bonus on creep provided too little of an advantage, especially when the generated creep area was relatively small. Since Zerg also lack units that can move across cliffs, they rely more heavily on flying transport units than other races.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Therefore, the Overlord now generates creep over a larger area, and creep increases the health regeneration of Zerg ground units instead of their movement speed. Since the speed bonus mainly benefited melee units, the Overlord previously had to fly directly over enemy forces, or at least get very close, to spread creep in a way that actually supported them. With the new changes to creep, however, it\u8217\'92s now valuable to spread creep under ranged units as well, allowing them to survive longer. This means the Overlord can position itself above or even behind its own army, rather than being within easy firing range of the enemy. As a result, the opponent faces an interesting choice: push forward to kill the Overlords and reduce the healing effect, or continue focusing on the rest of the Zerg army.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To give Zerg also more mobility starting from the early game, Ventral Sacs now requires the Evolution Chamber instead of the Lair. This means it\u8217\'92s no longer enough to block narrow ramps to keep the Zerg out of your own base, players must secure larger areas instead. In addition, the Overlord\u8217\'92s movement and turning speed have been reduced to reinforce the immersion that the Overlord is a rather slow creature and cannot instantly turn 180 degrees.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
040_Queen, larvae production, Zerg defense}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
In today\u8217\'92s video, I\u8217\'92ll be presenting the changes to the Queen, larvae production and Zerg defense.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
Until now, the Queen extended creep through Creep Tumors, provided additional larvae through Zerg main structures, and healed both buildings and units. The Queen was never meant to be an effective offensive unit, since she is very slow off creep and all of her abilities required either creep or a Zerg main structure. Due to the Zerg\u8217\'92s relatively weak static defenses and limited defensive options overall, it was previously necessary to rely on multiple strong Queens. In addition, each race was designed to have a mechanic that encouraged players to return to their base: for Terran it is Calldown: }{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
Mule}{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
., for Protoss Chrono Boost, and for Zerg Larvae Injection.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
To create more variety in gameplay, the Queen in }{\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
 is slightly weaker, while some of her abilities and other aspects of the Zerg have been strengthened. The Queen now has less health and her ability Larvae Injection has been reworked, Spore Crawlers are sturdier, Zerg ground units regenerate health faster on creep instead of moving faster, Burrow is more powerful, Creep Tumors can spawn 2 Broodlings or 1 Changeling, and Transfusion lasts longer. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
Unspent Creep Tumors now spawn two Broodlings when destroyed. They can also be manually consumed to spawn either two Broodlings, one Changeling, or an additional Creep Tumor. The Overseer loses the ability to spawn a Changeling and instead gains the ability to refresh Creep Tumors, allowing this ability to be reused. Refresh Creep Tumor can be autocast, creating a new mechanic of its own, adding immersion by having Overseers scattered across the map to refresh tumors. Players are also faced with a meaningful choice: whether to spread creep further, save tumors for defense, or use them to spawn Changelings. To reduce Changeling spam, Changelings now cost 1 supply. Near-unlimited scouting and detection options, similar to the Scan mechanic, are unhealthy. Scouting and detection should require deliberate, meaningful investment that rewards skill and does not always pay off.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
The Transfuse ability can once again be cast off creep and now lasts longer and making it more useful both defensively and offensively. Offensive mass Queens should still be less powerful, since Queens now have significantly less health and can be focused down more easily. In addition, the other races also have new defensive options.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
Larvae are now meant to be produced primarily through Zerg main structures. Building additional Hatcheries or upgrading them to Lair or Hive will automatically increase larva production, with Lair generating more than Hatchery and Hive generating more than Lair. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
The Queen can still create larvae without a Zerg main building, but at a higher energy cost. This ability is no longer meant to make up a large part of consistent larva production, but rather to serve as a limited tactical option anywhere on the map. Therefore Larvae now also survive for 10 seconds off creep so that the larvae can be morphed into eggs. This change removes the monotonous Larvae Injection mechanic, which was both a hurdle for beginners and tedious for more experienced players, allowing everyone to focus more on the engaging parts of the game. In addition the increased reliance on multiple Zerg main structures also enhances immersion, making Zerg bases feel more \u8220\'93Zergy\u8221\'94 again with more beehives instead of one.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\i0\loch
With simplified larva production, tumors spawning Broodlings or Changelings, longer-lasting Transfuse, Zerg ground units regenerating faster on creep, burrowed units taking 50% less damage and receiving a short speed boost upon unburrowing, Zerg are now much stronger in the early game. They can move out of their bases more confidently, establish map control earlier, and no longer have to wait until late game. Altogether, this creates more strategic possibilities and a more \u8220\'93Zerg-like\u8221\'94 feeling. The Queen\u8217\'92s ability to generate larvae is no longer mandatory, but instead a tactical option to create a limited number of larvae, even outside the bases.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
050_Zergling}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\fi0\li0\lin0\sb140\sa120\keepn{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ab0 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af9\langfe2052\loch
Today I\u8217\'92d like to introduce the changes to the Zergling.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
To make individual Zerglings easier to click on, to increase reaction options against incoming Zerglings, and to reduce the impact of area-of-effect damage on them, the Zergling model and its spacing to other units have been slightly increased, while its movement speed has been reduced.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
Of course, additional changes have also been introduced to create more opportunities for players to react to situations and to enable a wider variety of strategies and unit compositions.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
To achieve that, damage has to go down, health needs to go up, and speed has to be reduced, but without making the game feel too slow. The target audience here includes }{\rtlch\af6\ai \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i\b0\dbch\af9\loch
all}{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
 skill levels, not just pro players, not just beginners, and not only those in between.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
At this point, I define the best compromise differently from Blizzard and from some pro players or streamers. For an RTS to truly become \u8220\'93too slow\u8221\'94 for professional players, it would have to be slowed down far more than what I\u8217\'92m doing here. That risk is therefore very distant and will not be a topic in my upcoming videos.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
If anyone feels my mod is too slow overall or less fun, they can, of course, continue playing the original }{\rtlch\af6\ai \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i\b0\dbch\af9\loch
StarCraft II}{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
. What I\u8217\'92m offering here is simply an alternative. In the end, players who want more variety, more opportunities to react, and more comeback potential can play my mod. And those who don\u8217\'92t enjoy that style have the option to play what they find most fun.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
In }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b\dbch\af9\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
Zerglings are now slightly slower and larger, but they regenerate health on creep faster, take reduced damage while burrowed, gain a short speed boost after unburrowing, and benefit from generally reduced area-damage effects, refined movement mechanics, and the new army-split button. As some of you may already know from other videos, several other units now also move a bit slower than before.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
All of these options make Zerglings easier to control and give them more possibilities. How strong or weak they turn out to be will become clear over time with your help. That\u8217\'92s why it\u8217\'92s important to have plenty of matches and feedback, so we can discover the small imbalances together and fix them.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af9\loch
Thanks to the army-split button, even small groups of units can start to feel like larger armies, which enhances immersion. It\u8217\'92s no coincidence that Blizzard\u8217\'92s original Zerg showcase videos had much greater spacing between units, it made the Zerg look more swarmy. I want to bring that same feeling into actual gameplay, not just make it look good in promotional videos.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
060_Baneling}
