\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\sb140\sa120\keepn{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ab0 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92ll be introducing the changes to the }{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ab \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\cf0\fs24\lang1031\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
Baneling}{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ab0 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
In addition to the standard adjustments that most units have received, the Baneling now deals }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
significantly more damage to its primary target}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
. This makes Banelings more threatening to single units or small groups of tougher enemies.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Previously, Banelings could instantly kill too many units at once, a risk that has been reduced in }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 through many small tuning adjustments.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
The Baneling\u8217\'92s health has }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
not}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 been increased, since the combination of reduced incoming damage and the }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
speed boost after unburrowing}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 should already make it easier for them to reach their targets.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
At the same time, the }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Army Split Button}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 and other new mechanics provide additional ways to }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
mitigate Baneling damage}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
. Some of these tools depend more heavily on micro skill than others.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
For example, abilities like }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Defensive Matrix}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 require fast and precise unit selection, a much more demanding task than simply pressing the Army Split Button on the keyboard. The }{\rtlch\af6\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
speed boost after unburrowing}{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 helps counterbalance that somewhat, but it also demands smart positioning, good timing, and good micro control.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
070_Hydralisk}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\sb140\sa120\keepn{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ai\ab0 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af5\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\cf0\fs24\lang1031\i0\b0\kerning1\f5\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92ll be introducing the changes to the Hydralisk.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
In the original }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
StarCraft II}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
the Hydralisk is a glass cannon, a fragile unit that, due to its higher tech level, naturally comes with a higher cost. The question at the time was: }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Which attribute could Blizzard enhance to justify the Hydralisk\u8217\'92s tech level and cost?}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
The Zergling had already taken the role of high mobility, and the Roach filled the role of strong armor, which didn\u8217\'92t leave much else. So the answer seemed clear: the Hydralisk had to deal a lot of damage, since it couldn\u8217\'92t take much in return.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
So it was clear that the Hydralisk had to deal a lot of damage since it couldn\u8217\'92t take much itself. }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Blizzard also wanted every Tier 1.5 unit to feel completely new, to make }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
StarCraft II}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 stand apart from }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
StarCraft 1}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 and strike a balance between familiar and fresh gameplay, at least, that\u8217\'92s my interpretation and my claim.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Unfortunately, this focus underestimated the importance of gameplay depth and sacrificed too much of it just to make }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
StarCraft II}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 feel newer and more innovative.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
As a result, the Roach became a Tier 1.5 unit, a cheap, tanky unit that would actually make far more sense as a }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Tier 2}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 unit. Tanky units usually shouldn\u8217\'92t be available in large numbers, because they can easily become too strong, especially when they\u8217\'92re ranged units.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
To avoid too much overlap with the Zergling, Blizzard made the Roach from a melee unit to a ranged unit. To also avoid too much overlap with the Hydralisk, Blizzard made the Roach unable to attack air units. After all, you need hard counters against mass-producible tanky units. }{\rtlch\af6\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
And since we\u8217\'92re talking about Zerg, it would also feel strange if the Tier 1.5 unit couldn\u8217\'92t be produced in large numbers.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
The idea behind the Roach wasn\u8217\'92t bad, it works reasonably well, but I believe it has }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
much more potential as a Tier 2 unit}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
. Moving it up would also open the door for the Zerg to have an }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
early-game anti-air unit}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 that\u8217\'92s actually effective at moving out of the base and taking the fight to the opponent. The Hydralisk would be perfect for that role, but because }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
StarCraft II}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 needed to look and feel \u8220\'93new and different,\u8221\'94 gameplay quality suffered as a result. And we all know how much Zerg struggles in professional matches when they\u8217\'92re forced to play defensively until the late game. Thankfully, I have different priorities. So in }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
I\u8217\'92ve }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
swapped the roles of the Hydralisk and the Roach}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
making the Hydralisk a }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Tier 1.5 unit}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
This gives Zerg players an early anti-air option that also works well offensively and creates }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
more strategic possibilities}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
. Meanwhile, the Roach can now fully realize its potential as a }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Tier 2}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 unit, it can be more expensive, tankier, and come with strong abilities like }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Burrow Movement}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 right from the start. The design challenges and solutions around Burrow Movement will be discussed in the Roach video.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
As a Tier 1.5 unit, the }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Hydralisk}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 is now }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
cheaperdeals less damage}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
and has }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
many upgrades}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 that keep it relevant later in the game. It counters Zerglings and Banelings }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
less harshly}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 than the Roach did, but still performs well against them, especially with increasing levels of micro skill.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
The new }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
defensive tools}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 available to Zerg also make it easier to counter Zerglings and Banelings even without relying on the Hydralisk. For example, Creep Tumors can now }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
spawn two Broodlings}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
workers can }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
enter the main building to deploy Broodlings}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
and the }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Spine Crawler\u8217\'92s size has been increased}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 to help block enemy units more effectively. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
One could argue that Zerg intentionally don\u8217\'92t have an early anti-air unit capable of moving out offensively, in order to emphasize the differences between the races.\line But in my opinion, the price you pay for that in terms of gameplay and strategic diversity is too high.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
080_Overseer}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\sb140\sa120\keepn{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\i0\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92ll be introducing the changes to the }{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ai0\ab \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\cf0\fs24\lang1031\i0\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
Overseer}{\rtlch\af6\afs24\alang1081\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\i0\b0\kerning1\f4\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Since the Overseer has energy and only two energy-based abilities, both of which are offensive, I thought it would make sense to add a new }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
defensive ability}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
.\line This new ability is called }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Incubate Tumor}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
which allows the Overseer to refresh existing Creep Tumors so they can use their abilities again.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
This fits the Overseer, and the Zerg in general, very well, because the Zerg don\u8217\'92t just spread }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
creep}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
they spread }{\rtlch\af6\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
life}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
. The feeling of a living swarm is further enhanced by the fact that it now makes sense for Overseers to fly over areas covered in creep.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Since }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Incubate Tumor}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 can even be set to }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
autocast}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
players can create patrol routes for their Overseers. That way, they can not only detect invisible units but also automatically refresh spent Tumors, either to support creep spread or to strengthen defenses.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Additionally, Overseers can no longer spawn Changelings, Creep Tumors now handle this instead. This gives players another reason to spread Creep Tumors and refresh them with Overseers.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af7\loch
To further differentiate the Overseer from the Observer, Oversight has been removed and replaced with Telepathic Suppression. Like Oversight, Telepathic Suppression immobilizes the Overseer once activated, costs no energy, and prevents enemy energy-based abilities from being used in its radius. This gives the Overseer a combat-relevant ability that forces opponents to either fight without their energy-dependent units or treat Overseers as a genuine threat that must be eliminated first.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Contaminate}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
 has also been adjusted: instead of completely stopping unit production or research in affected structures, it now }{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
slows them down for a longer duration and creates creep in a medium-sized area}{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
. This change makes comebacks more feasible, since production and research aren\u8217\'92t entirely halted. At the same time, Zerg players can make better use of the longer-lasting effect, and it becomes more rewarding to send Overseers into dangerous areas to contaminate enemy structures. Especially before a direct attack with Zerg units.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\af6\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Overall, these changes increase the Overseer\u8217\'92s versatility, open up new strategic and tactical possibilities and }{\rtlch\af6 \ltrch\dbch\af7\loch
increases the swarm feeling and thus the immersion.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
090_Swarm Host}
