Roach remains highly durable while underground.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
By default, the Roach now moves just as fast burrowed as it does unburrowed. After the Tunneling claws upgrade burrowed Roaches move 30% faster. All these changes allow the Roach\u8217\'92s effectiveness to scale better with micro, the higher your micro skill, the more you can get out of the unit, similar to Blink micro. You now want to burrow Roaches when they\u8217\'92re low on health, since they take less damage and regenerate faster while underground. And if you need to retreat, it also makes more sense to burrow them, since they move just as fast underground as they do above ground, and even faster when they have the Tunneling Claws upgrade.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af7\loch
Moreover, the Roach now deals significantly more damage against structures. This makes it well-suited for sneaking into an enemy base and sniping important structures. Its high movement speed and durability while burrowed also help it escape safely after such attacks.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
120_Infestor}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Infestor.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
In the original Starcraft 2 the Infestor has the abilities }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Fungal Growth}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
which slows enemies and deals damage over time; }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Microbial Shroud}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
which reduces incoming damage from air and ranged units within a targeted area; and }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Neural Parasite}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
which temporarily takes control of an enemy unit while the Infestor must remain close to it.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Fungal Growth}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 has the weakness that its projectile is very difficult to dodge and it slows too heavily, leaving little room for reaction. However, players generally want to be able to react to things as much as possible, so I want to change Fungal Growth as follows:\line Fungal Growth now reduces the }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
armor}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 and }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
shield armor}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 of affected ground units instead of slowing and damaging air and ground units. Additionally, if a unit affected by Fungal Growth dies while under its effect, it spawns }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
two Broodlings}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
This change makes it easier to respond to the new Fungal Growth through healing and other defensive abilities, especially after being hit by it. Once units are affected, players will want to keep those specific units alive rather than the unaffected units, since their deaths would otherwise spawn additional enemy units that deal damage. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Microbial Shroud has been changed and moved to the Viper. In return, the Infestor now has Parasitic Bomb, allowing for an effective answer to mass air units earlier in the game. More details regarding the changes to Microbial Shroud will be covered in the video about the Viper changes. \line The energy cost and damage against non-armored units of Parasitic Bomb have been slightly reduced, while its range, duration, and damage against armored units have been increased.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Since }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Neural Parasite}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 is also a high-risk, high-reward ability that is mainly effective only against expensive late-game units, I wanted to replace it with a new ability that is more useful across all stages of the game and against a wider range of units. Therefore, }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Neural Parasite}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 has been removed and replaced with }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Plague Cloud}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Plague Cloud}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 continuously deals low}{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
 damage}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 to ground units over a }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
large area}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 for a long period of time. It can be used as a }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
damage boost}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 in long engagements, such as breaking or preventing sieges. In addition, Plague Cloud can serve as a }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
harassment tool}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
since it doesn\u8217\'92t deal its full damage instantly but over time, forcing the affected player to periodically pull workers away from resources to heal, repair, or recharge shields. As a result, players will want to }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
avoid being hit by Plague Cloud at all costs}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
which means keeping Infestors at a distance.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
In addition to its new abilities, all of the Infestor\u8217\'92s existing abilities can now be used while burrowed, greatly increasing its versatility. However, the Infestor now moves much more slowly when burrowed. Like all burrowed units, it takes 50% less damage and receives a brief speed boost upon unburrowing, allowing it to retreat more easily. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
This updated set of Infestor abilities enables many new strategies, and each ability now has the potential to be seen more frequently, especially since all of them can now be cast }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
while burrowed}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
. In addition, the mechanical and visual design of its abilities now align more closely with its latest concept art from before }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i\b0\loch
Wings of Liberty}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 was released.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
130_Mutalisk + Spire}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Mutalisk. To make Mutalisks more appealing, the bounce range and damage of their attacks have been slightly increased, while the cost and build time of the Spire have been significantly reduced. The Spire now costs the same amount of resources and takes the same build time as the Roach Warren and Infestation Pit, making every \line T 2.5 option similarly accessible.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
140_Corrupter}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Corruptor.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
The Corruptor is the Zerg\u8217\'92s anti-air unit, which is also very effective against structures thanks to its }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Caustic Spray}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 ability.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Since the Viper has a very strong weapon against structures, making it somewhat overlap with Caustic Spray, even if it deals less damage, and to make the Corruptor useful against a wider range of targets, I have }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
removed Caustic Spray}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 and replaced it with a new ability called }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Corruption}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Corruption}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 is a cooldown-based ability with a relatively short cooldown that can be cast on individual ground or air units. It deals continuous damage over time until the target reaches a minimum of 1 HP. This makes Corruption a potentially very annoying ability for opponents, as it introduces a new form of harassment that can repeatedly force them to heal, repair, or recharge their shields.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Because of this, the Corruptor can also serve as an }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
anti-ground alternative}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 to the Mutalisk, though it functions a bit differently since it cannot deliver killing blows. You\u8217\'92ll still need other units to finish off targets, making the Corruptor function more as a }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
support unit}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 alongside its harassment potential. Against air units, the Corruptor is now also stronger. Whether this causes balance issues remains to be seen, as all three races have received new and improved anti-air options. Additionally, the Corruptor now }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
costs more minerals and less gas}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
making it easier to combine with gas-heavy units such as the }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Swarm Host}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 or }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Infestor}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Overall, the Corruptor has gained new use cases, opening up new possibilities for }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
unit compositions and strategies}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
150_Nydus_Worm}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af8
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Nydus Network and Nydus Worm.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Nydus Worms can transport an unlimited number of units across the map in a very short time. This ability is extremely powerful, in my opinion, too powerful. This is also one of the reasons why usually only a single Nydus Worm is needed, which feels less \u8220\'93Zerg-like.\u8221\'94 In addition, the creep spread of the Nydus Worm is so large that it\u8217\'92s harder to spawn it in a hidden location. Because of this, a single moment of inattention from the opponent can make the Nydus Worm so powerful that it often ends the game.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To make individual Nydus Worms easier to counter, each Nydus Worm can now only spawn 16 units before going on cooldown, after which it can spawn another 16 units. To encourage using multiple, more hidden Nydus Worms, the Nydus Network cost and the Nydus Worm\u8217\'92s creep spread have been reduced. At the same time, the cost of the Nydus Worm has been slightly increased to make every failed use of the Nydus Worm more punishing. To ensure that Zerg players can still easily move their armies between their bases, Nydus Networks can still spawn an unlimited number of units without cooldown. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
This makes it easier to build multiple Nydus Networks and to use several Nydus Worms simultaneously. This feels more \u8220\'93Zerg-like,\u8221\'94 while at the same time a single Nydus Worm can no longer unload unlimited units continuously, making multiple Nydus Worms necessary when using them in a more obvious and aggressive manner. However, if you pursue a longer-term strategy where the Nydus Worms are meant to remain undetected, a single Nydus Worm can still be sufficient, since its reduced creep spread makes it harder to spot.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af8\loch
160_Viper}
