\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Blinding Cloud was an ability with very limited counterplay. Players could either preemptively build more melee units, of which there are very few, or be forced to retreat. However, give}{\loch
n the pace of StarCraft II, retreating often meant certain death for units like the Siege Tank, which couldn\u8217\'92t move away quickly enough. \line Infested Terrans, on the other hand, can be thrown inside the minimum range of Siege Tanks, causing them to be attacked only by nearby units that may deal splash damage to their own Siege Tanks if the Infested Terrans aren\u8217\'92t destroyed quickly enough. In addition, Infested Terrans can be used as a harassment option or temporarily as part of the main army.\line \line }{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Microbial Shroud reduces incoming ranged damage in a targeted area for a certain duration. However, its main issue is that it becomes a target for area-of-effect abilities such as Psi Storm, which can quickly turn its benefits into disadvantages.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
As a result, Microbial Shroud has been reworked. It now has a larger area of effect, lasts longer, and reduces the attack and vision range of all enemy air units within the area to 2. This encourages players to use it primarily against enemy air units, forcing them to withdraw from the affected zone. It works very similarly to Blinding Cloud, except that air units are generally better able to counter it than ground units. Air units are more mobile, cannot block each other\u8217\'92s movement, and can retreat freely in any direction without being limited by terrain. Additionally, Protoss air armies are especially strong against Zerg, which is why a stronger counter in this area is necessary. \line To better reflect its new functionality, Microbial Shroud has been renamed to Blinding Spores.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
With the changes to Consume and the addition of Infested Terran, the Viper can now operate independently against ground units, smaller armies, and structures. At the same time, it still performs excellently as a support unit within your army, especially against air units, thanks to Abduct and Blinding Spores.}
