\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\dbch\af7\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Broodlord.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\dbch\af7\loch
The Broodlord is, on the one hand, quite vulnerable because it moves relatively slowly, but on the other hand, once a critical mass is reached, Broodlords become extremely powerful, especially when supported by an army. Their broodlings block all enemy ground units and prevent them from reaching the Broodlords. The few units that can get into range, such as Blink Stalkers, are usually in great danger from other units protecting the Broodlords and often end up being sacrificed. Once Stalkers have blinked in, they can\u8217\'92t blink back out quickly enough, as the broodlings also block their retreat path.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\dbch\af7\loch
In addition, the Broodlord\u8217\'92s initial projectile already deals significant damage, making the broodlings themselves often less important when it comes to sniping small groups of units that get dangerously close. The broodlings also have a very short lifespan.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\dbch\af7\loch
All of this means that Broodlords are very difficult to counter without air units, but at the same time, they are easy to counter when used alone or in small numbers without army support.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\dbch\af7\loch
To make the Broodlord more viable on its own and in smaller numbers, the lifespan and damage of the broodlings, as well as the Broodlord\u8217\'92s movement speed, acceleration and weapon range, have been increased. To make it easier to counter Broodlords in larger numbers or when supported by an army, the broodlings\u8217\'92 HP, movement speed and the Broodlord\u8217\'92s initial damage, and its attack speed have been reduced. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\dbch\af7\loch
This should give players more options with and against the Broodlord.}
\par }